AN ACT relating to property; requiring a landlord of a premises [comprised of]
comprising more than [200] 100 dwelling units to establish a policy
requiring certain applicants for employment to undergo a criminal
background check as a condition of employment; requiring such a
landlord to take certain actions relating to dwelling unit keys; requiring
such a landlord to [provide certain proof upon the request of certain
persons or governmental entities;] maintain a log of certain
information and actions on the premises; and providing other
matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires certain persons who work for a landlord of dwelling units intended
2 and operated exclusively for certain older persons to undergo a criminal background check as
3 a condition of employment with the landlord. (NRS 118A.335) Section 1 of this bill requires a
4 landlord of a premises [comprised of] comprising more than [200] 100 dwelling units to
5 establish: (1) a policy requiring certain applicants for employment to undergo a criminal
6 background check as a condition of employment; and (2) certain written policies and
7 procedures relating to dwelling unit keys. Section 1 also requires any such landlord to [: (1)]
8 maintain on the premises: (1) a log that accounts for the issuance and return of each dwelling
9 unit key; and (2) [upon the request of certain persons or governmental entities, provide proof
10 of compliance with the requirements prescribed by] the written policies and procedures
11 relating to dwelling unit keys established pursuant to section 1.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 118A of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto a new
2 section to read as follows:
3 1. A landlord of a premises [comprised of] comprising more than [200] 100
4 dwelling units attached to a single parcel of property shall establish:
5 (a) A policy requiring an applicant for employment with the landlord to
6 undergo a criminal background check as a condition of employment if the

